Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.93,0:00:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for helping me.\NAnd my question has to do with prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.33,0:00:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NPrayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.51,0:01:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My question has to do with prayer.\NAnd since September 8th is going to be a big unity prayer day,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.31,0:01:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel compelled to participate in the prayer day.\NAnd my question is, in a group like this, with all of us together with intention of prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,could we raise the consciousness of the world by joining together on that day to pray?\NIt's not a cause and effect relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.76,0:01:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a contribution.\NBy ourselves, we can't lift the level of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.34,0:01:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But all of humanity together by intention constantly raises the level of the ocean.\NAnd everyone floating on the ocean gets lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.88,0:01:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But not by cause and effect.\NBut by virtue of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.98,0:02:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By your intention of what you have become.\NSo you contribute to the overall field, and the field is what lifts people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we did it in a group, if I went to a group to pray, the intention of the group...\NI don't know whether...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's numerical causality again.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.91,0:02:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we have permission to ask this.\NA group prayer is more efficacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.18,0:02:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More efficacious in raising the level of mankind than just individual prayer resistance.\NGroup prayer is, yes, efficacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm glad you mentioned it.\NBecause what is the date again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.97,0:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot it.\NSeptember the 8th.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.09,0:02:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,September the 8th is Unity Prayer Day.\NI forgot to mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.99,0:02:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I had that on my list to mention it.\NUnity, annual Unity Prayer Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.87,0:02:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo that's a powerful time for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.27,0:02:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an excellent time to pray.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:02:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NHi, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Susan.\NWell, my question is, I'm an interpreter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.15,0:03:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I speak several languages.\NAnd to work, I do it automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.74,0:03:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can be...\NI'm able now to just witness the interpretation process and step back of it and just witness what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I started...\NWhen I started reading and studying your material, I realized that it was good for me to start knowing something about meditation because I was clueless and I started working on the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.87,0:04:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of a sudden, one day I was driving and I realized for a second that there's no separation.\NThere is no out there and in the in here, and I felt a huge vertigo, like I need to hang on to and hold on to something because I felt like it was weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.18,0:04:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I on the right path or I need a doctor?\NYeah, you're on the right path.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.93,0:04:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditating when you're driving may not be the best deal.\NYes, there's a reorientation because of the shift of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.96,0:05:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you go into a really incredible space, you may not be able to function for periods of time because where you are in space and people keep talking to the body and you've got nothing to do with the body and they think it's you.\NSo it has to do with reorienting yourself within a new context.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of strangeness disappears.\NYou just keep surrendering and praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it settles down.\NAnd then it settles down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.21,0:05:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It settles down.\NIt's like wearing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.59,0:05:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,different glasses, very similar to wearing different glasses.\NYou can actually see better than you could before, but there's a reorientation and that's how you felt was that reorienting yourself to a shifted context.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.83,0:05:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, devotion and spiritual will.\NIs devotion a quality of the spiritual will?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:05:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is devotion a quality of the spiritual will?\NIs devotion a quality of the spiritual will?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.72,0:06:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it the same thing where I just forget about it and just keep doing what I'm doing?\NWill is more like a stated intention, a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.63,0:06:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And devotion is more dedication and love.\NWhen you combine the two, you have devotional non-duality, which is the book I'm finishing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.24,0:06:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You have devotion to truth.\NYou have devotion to truth, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.64,0:06:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What gives it power is not only intention, which can be just mental.\NBut also the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.34,0:06:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And devotion comes from the heart.\NSo the power of the heart then energizing the will and reason and intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.50,0:06:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:07:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it right.\NI've heard you talk a lot about the 400s and the 500s, but between 500 and enlightenment is the 600s.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.61,0:07:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you haven't mentioned much that I've heard about that.\NAnd you haven't mentioned much that I've heard about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.11,0:07:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you haven't mentioned much that I've heard about that.\NAre there any milestones in the 600s or things to let go of?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are, we're going to, we're doing the levels now.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.16,0:07:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, we do the levels below 200.\NThen we go from 200 up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.32,0:07:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NFrom 600 up are the levels, specifically, formally, those of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.76,0:07:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sat Chittananda, Silent Bliss is at 600.\NThe problem of how to get from 600 on up is infrequent because most people leave at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.31,0:08:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Some continue on, you know.\NBut without motivation to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.66,0:08:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In 600, there is no motivation.\NEverything is perfect, still, infinite, peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It would not come up that there is anything further.\NSo anything you learned about it would probably be useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyhow.\NThere is that which is, it does not seem possible to the ego that there is anything beyond 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everything is peaceful.\NThere's nothing that you desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you fear.\NWhether the body continues on or not is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.49,0:08:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite stillness, peace, and bliss.\NConsciousness, then, of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.42,0:08:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But apparently, if it's not.\NBut apparently, if it's karmically attuned to do so, will continue on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.96,0:09:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And even rarer still, it will go on up higher and higher.\NUsually in the 700s, it will stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The best known sages of recent decades.\NIn 700 and something, it just stays there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.57,0:09:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a karmic propensity.\NAnd then it may start, extremely rarely, to move on up even higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.61,0:09:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know when it's doing that.\NBecause there's a considerable discomfort at 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.64,0:09:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The nerves feel like they're on fire.\NThe slightest thing that's out will make it quite severe, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.98,0:09:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're beyond personal karma.\NNow what's holding you up is something from the collective consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:10:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To which you have ascribed due to humanness.\NAt 800, you begin really sort of agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.23,0:10:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dedication to continue on is what drives you through it.\NAt that level, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.98,0:10:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The information needed to transcend that level came in the form of finding a copy of a Buddhist text\Nin the drawer of some foreign country.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.78,0:10:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And recalling that the Buddha said his bones felt like they were broken.\NAt that point, it became okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.10,0:10:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.91,0:11:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A group of us who are here today, some of us are here today,\Nrecently were around a swami who manifested jewelry and vibhuti, holy ash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.20,0:11:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd we want to know if this phenomenon of manifesting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can happen when the teacher is below 540.\NAnd perhaps more importantly, what is the purpose of manifesting these objects
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if it is indeed happening?\NWhat does this really have to do with enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.15,0:11:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what all that has to do with enlightenment.\NBut we have permission to do vibhuti.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Vibhuti calibrates over 200.\NVibhuti calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,199.\NVibhuti calibrates around 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.40,0:11:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it has to do with confusing.\NIt's really, it has to do, I've written a chapter on the cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,S-I-D-D-H-I-S.\NSo these are the phenomena, paranormal phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.56,0:12:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They begin to occur in the 500s.\NBecome quite marked around 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.00,0:12:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Become almost continuous.\NThe miraculous is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're clairvoyant, clairaudient.\NThe miraculous is the common.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.09,0:12:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You hold a parking place in space in mind.\NAnd when you get there, there it is naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.28,0:12:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Various phenomena.\NThe so-called miraculous occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.28,0:12:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the consequences of kundalini energy.\NIt has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.66,0:12:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person identifies them and begins to,\Nyou have no control over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.20,0:12:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy does what it does under the direction of the Holy Spirit.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.33,0:12:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo what she's talking about is,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:13:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with magic control.\NIt has to do with the egotism of the cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.18,0:13:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with claiming the cities\Nas a consequence of one's personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.18,0:13:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's okay.\NSo it's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.60,0:13:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what impresses the public.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So it, could it be then dangerous because it...\NTo seek it for its own sake, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.60,0:13:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to seek the cities is obviously an ego,\Nattraction to the spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.60,0:13:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To merely want to be able to levitate, fly,\Nand all those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.85,0:13:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is obviously an attraction to the spiritual ego.\NThose things are spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.14,0:13:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Spontaneous.\NJust like the miraculous is spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.20,0:13:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody is brought to have lunch with you.\NYou look at them and suddenly you get from the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.20,0:13:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they've brought you...\NThey brought her because she has something terribly wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.20,0:14:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're hoping for a miracle.\NSo you look at the person with the love you feel towards all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.13,0:14:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and include them in the divinity of the presence\Nand then either cures or doesn't cure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.13,0:14:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with you at all.\NSometimes they walk away cured.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.22,0:14:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens of its own.\NSo there is no person doing miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.22,0:14:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no performer of miracles\Nbecause the miraculous is the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of divinity as the whole field\Nwhich then pulls forth the karmic,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the karmic propensity.\NSo the apple falls from the tree
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.22,0:14:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's karmically ripe.\NNot because you are causing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.22,0:14:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So we witness the miraculous.\NAnd it's always spontaneous of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.99,0:14:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no me causing that.\NThere's no this causing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So why jewelry?\NI don't know. The glamour of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.99,0:15:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NGlamour of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Theatrics of it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.49,0:15:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.12,0:15:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I hide this?\NOh, here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.81,0:15:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question that's along the lines\Nwith what we were just talking about, levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.97,0:15:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And in reading your material and your lectures\Nyou state that the ego gets transcended
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.32,0:15:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at level 600.\NAnd something that keeps sticking to my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.36,0:15:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when you talked about Muhammad,\Nwhen he calibrated at 700
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.55,0:16:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and through almost a simplistic misinterpretation\Nof the sword of truth made a great fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.55,0:16:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He was attacked by the Luciferic energy.\NBecause as you get higher, you get attacked by that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.09,0:16:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the enemy of truth.\NBecause truth will reduce its dominion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.09,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're attacked by the demons.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, a book on truth versus falsehood,\Nhow popular do you think that's going to make you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.66,0:16:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThat's why I waited until I was older.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.07,0:16:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NWhen you tell the truth, quickly you leave town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm prepared, you know.\NSo it has nothing to do with ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.07,0:16:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with an ego structure\Nwhere something was offered, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in some sort of power, you know, control.\NOr anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.07,0:16:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was more of an attack, you said.\NYou're saying that happened to Muhammad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.23,0:17:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he had a vulnerability\Nand the Luciferic saw the energy and shot into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.86,0:17:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The same happens with alcohol intoxication.\NYou know, demonic possession is very frequent in intoxication.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.86,0:17:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he will take over the domination.\NSo when he had a temporal epileptic fit, see,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.86,0:17:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,his defense was down and the energy saw fit.\NSo it reversed mercy and turned evil into good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.95,0:17:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the classic Luciferic conversion.\NThe worship, you know, as Ben Laden says when he comes on,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we worship death, you worship life.\NThat is the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that is not a traversable.\NThat is not a traversable track.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.07,0:17:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand that?\NThat is not traversable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:18:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet.\NIt's 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you traverse 180?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.19,0:18:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.09,0:18:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you what happened with this person,\Nthis entity here, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.09,0:18:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In a very high space, beyond all personal karma,\Ncame out of nowhere a silent knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.53,0:18:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of a temptation.\NI mean, I see it as a temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.53,0:18:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It came as a silent attraction\Nvia a non-verbal knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.30,0:18:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you realize you've transcended all personal karma,\Nthat there is no accountability,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,all power is yours, own it.\NThat's what the knowingness said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.20,0:18:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Inasmuch as I couldn't see what the hell you want to do with power,\Nit'd be a drag and a nuisance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.27,0:19:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the self is all that is,\NI turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, very few people have been there,\Nso I saw who was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.26,0:19:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw the answers they gave, yeah?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.26,0:19:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called the Luciferian temptation, yeah?\NIt came to Jesus Christ in the Gethsemane.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.20,0:19:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you advance, we haven't gotten that far yet.\NBut when we get advanced to the levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.20,0:19:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we sort of look at, we did the levels below 200,\Nbecause they're the most painful,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when people get their foot out of the bear trap.\NBut then the higher levels will go,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the very highest levels.\NIn transcending levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I go into the 600s, 700s, 800s,\Nand up, and I do in devotional non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.65,0:19:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very limited audience for that kind of information,\Nso I'm not going to take up the public's time with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.97,0:20:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But for people who are driven,\Ndriven in sort of a spiritual insanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.45,0:20:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you're willing to go through hell to get to it.\NSome people will get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To have heard of the truth will then\Nsummon forth from the vibration and the aura
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to the knowingness of what to do with that temptation.\NWhy would you choose that which you already are?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.54,0:20:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be denying the reality of what you are already,\Nto say, well, I choose power over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.76,0:20:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very hot question.\NHow about an easy one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.10,0:20:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see what I can do.\NFirst, I want to thank you again
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.04,0:20:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for the incredible work you do.\NYou just helped me in my life in so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.04,0:20:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This book, Truth vs. Falsehood,\Nreally forced me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.04,0:20:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you put the caveat in the beginning.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.04,0:20:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You do pay attention to the caveat.\NYes, I paid attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.04,0:21:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I waited until I could handle it,\Nwhich I don't know if I still could,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.04,0:21:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but thank you.\NSomebody said,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.04,0:21:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just ouch, ouch, ouch, taking off band-aids.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.04,0:21:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We got an email this week that said,\Nreading your book is ouch, ouch, ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like ripping off band-aids.\NVery true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.97,0:21:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,See, people get so attached to their view\Nthat it's painful to let their view go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.97,0:21:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.97,0:21:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually wrote a letter of apology\Nto President Bush
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.97,0:21:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because I felt so bad.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.97,0:21:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.\NHe's a human being like you or I.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.74,0:21:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably does the best he thinks\Nin the situation he's in,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.74,0:21:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wouldn't take his job\Nfor all the money in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.93,0:21:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you.\NBecause no matter what you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be made wrong,\Nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.93,0:21:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Very true.\NI have one comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.93,0:21:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI'm a little disappointed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.93,0:21:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.93,0:22:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because you have the Fortune 500 companies.\NI work for Best Buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.93,0:22:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't listed there.\NI was waiting to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.93,0:22:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not in there.\NDo you know what they calibrate at?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.93,0:22:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I do.\NOh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.93,0:22:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't.\NI think we did some of them in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.93,0:22:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's some,\Nbut Best Buy wasn't listed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.83,0:22:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And not the one that you want to buy,\Nyeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.83,0:22:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.34,0:22:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.34,0:22:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.34,0:22:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the one that you want to buy,\Nyeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no.\NI work for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.34,0:22:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you work for them.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.27,0:22:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nif you read literature like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.27,0:22:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you develop an intuitive eye.\NYeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.27,0:22:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you know, that's a fact.\NI mean, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.27,0:22:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we've done thousands.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.27,0:22:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody will hand me a book\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.27,0:22:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think this calibrates?\NA number shoots into my head already,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.27,0:22:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,240.\NI already know what it's likely going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.27,0:22:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NBut I wait until I verify it, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.68,0:23:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nand as I start to turn to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.68,0:23:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as I start to use the arm,\Nwe'll go up, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.68,0:23:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say,\Nit's 270,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.68,0:23:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's 275,\Nit's 280.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.68,0:23:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes down at 280.\NShe said,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.68,0:23:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it went out at 275.\NThe energy shot down at 275,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.68,0:23:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it takes the muscles that long to respond.\NBut she got the flash of the energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.68,0:23:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.48,0:23:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You work for a specific company or a group?\NNo,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.48,0:23:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Best Buy Company Incorporated.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.48,0:23:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Best Buy Company Incorporated.\NThat's what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.48,0:23:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nthe yellow tag people?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.48,0:23:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes,\Nyellow tag people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.48,0:23:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nyeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.60,0:23:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah,\Nyeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.60,0:23:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThey're the one that have the,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.60,0:23:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call a squad now?\NYeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.60,0:23:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the Geek Squad.\NWhat do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.60,0:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Geek Squad.\NGeek Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.60,0:23:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\NI love the idea of a Geek Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.60,0:23:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I would go for them just for the Geek Squad.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.60,0:23:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a couple of Geek Squad people come to our house from playing.\NMan,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.60,0:23:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they were good.\NShoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.60,0:24:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,man,\Nall of our staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.60,0:24:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nwe were completely puzzled.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.60,0:24:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys,\Nthey're real,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.60,0:24:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they really are good geeks.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.60,0:24:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Njust the fact that you added geeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.60,0:24:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll vote for you.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.60,0:24:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.60,0:24:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,my actual question is,\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.28,0:24:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when the spiritual intention is set,\Nor the spiritual will and intention is set,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.28,0:24:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,does it kind of speed up karma,\Nkarma clearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.28,0:24:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Does karma just kind of,\Nas you're moving forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.28,0:24:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,karma just kind of come up quicker and quicker?\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.25,0:24:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,each step,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.02,0:24:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,eases,\Nopens the door to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.08,0:24:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It like waits,\Nbecause it's like a sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.08,0:24:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nas you move this,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.12,0:24:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you move,\Nremove that block,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.12,0:24:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and that avalanche falls of its own weight.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.40,0:24:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.33,0:25:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I intuit that it's an interiorist company.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.16,0:25:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.25,0:25:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep my job.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.25,0:25:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an interiorist company.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.64,0:25:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an interiorist company.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.64,0:25:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.64,0:25:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I just get the energy of it,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.64,0:25:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Njust the geek squad alone will tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.64,0:25:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,These are sharp people,\Nprobably in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.64,0:25:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NYou got to be at least in the 400s to be a geek.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.64,0:25:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes brains.\NIt takes brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.11,0:25:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be a dumbbell and be a geek.\NAnd dumbbells wouldn't work for a dumb company.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.16,0:25:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Njust the fact that geeks work for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.16,0:25:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,already tells me something about the company.\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.28,0:25:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A while back,\NI heard you talk about recontextualizing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.28,0:25:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe my own situation\Nor someone else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.66,0:25:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other day,\NI was in the lunchroom
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.66,0:25:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and someone's going on and on\Nabout the wrath of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.66,0:26:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I opened my mouth.\NAnd I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.58,0:26:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\NGod is love to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.58,0:26:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NInstead of wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.58,0:26:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And after I went home,\NI was thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.87,0:26:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nit got carried away,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.87,0:26:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the conversation.\NYou punched him?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.87,0:26:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who thinks God's love is going to get it from me.\NDidn't you say a while back
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.16,0:26:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you're in that type of situation\Nthat someone who's aware of what's going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.16,0:26:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they just say,\Nso,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.03,0:26:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so it seems\Nor something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.22,0:26:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It just,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.22,0:26:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.80,0:26:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it just,\Nit just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.80,0:26:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it just,\Nit just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.80,0:26:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it just,\Nit just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.80,0:26:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it just,\Nit just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.80,0:26:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it just,\Nit just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.80,0:26:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it just,\Nit just,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.80,0:26:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,right?\NHe should have let that opportunity go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.80,0:26:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They should have said,\Nalso,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.18,0:26:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,see,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.18,0:26:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.18,0:27:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nyeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.66,0:27:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they brought up your spiritual night\Nand you defended the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.66,0:27:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.82,0:27:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI felt kind of bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.82,0:27:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I quit giving up,\Ngetting up the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.82,0:27:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,see.\NI had a terrible time with the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.82,0:27:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nbecause I hadn't looked at the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.88,0:27:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nin a long,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.88,0:27:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,long time.\NAnd then when I did
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.88,0:27:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,God you know okay yeah thank you yeah thank you very much yes since I've met\Nyou the first time I recognize a lot of distractions in my life mainly mental
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.54,0:28:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,distractions and I want to know is there anything what I can do what kind of\Nmental disruptions like watching TV like gossiping like too much working at the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.36,0:28:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,computer this kind of stuff Oh distractions you know I see what you're\Nsaying yeah you get caught in distractions yeah yes instead of being
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.84,0:28:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,focused on the spiritual work yeah okay so you apply the spiritual principles to\Nthe distractions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.89,0:28:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all what does this mean it means what are you juicing out of it the\Nexcitement the drama the glamour are you willing to surrender that let it go you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.15,0:28:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,know what do you get out of it again what do you think is the game could you\Nsurrender the game yeah and then again on the other side what is the aversion
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.58,0:28:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say people seek entertainment all the time that's the attraction the\Nexcitement that the vicarious participation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.06,0:29:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and other people's lives in the drama then the aversion is to let it go\Nbecause then I'll be bored well I think about I'll start thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.20,0:29:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,about my worries instead of the distraction so you look at what's the\Nattraction and what's the aversion see what is the attraction and what is the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.17,0:29:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,aversion yeah what's the resistance what's the pull this way and what's the\Nresistance to be free of the world is not a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.92,0:29:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment, to have neither attraction nor aversion, which is different than non-attachment,\Nwhich is different, I'm sorry, than detachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.64,0:30:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Detachment is more like neutrality, but its downside can be flatness, non-participation.\NIt can lead to a sort of a voidness, a negation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.22,0:30:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to be neither attracted nor have an aversion.\NI have the feeling I can see it quite clearly, but it feels like a lack of surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.84,0:30:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But it feels like what?\NLack of surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.54,0:30:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the resistance of surrendering?\NIt's the fear of...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.96,0:30:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you've got to become conscious of it.\NYou have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.23,0:30:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In your investigation, what is the reluctance to surrendering?\NIt means you want to maintain control, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.80,0:30:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd what is your fear of letting go of control?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.98,0:30:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...\NSee, so you go inside questioning yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.51,0:31:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you find the answer.\NThe ego survives on control, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.51,0:31:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to resist, yeah?\NThe ego is not going to be happy that you want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.73,0:31:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Reduce its dominance in your life, huh?\NSo it's a natural resistance of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.62,0:31:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is narcissistically sovereign.\NIt's not going to welcome your attempts to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.38,0:31:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It will find excuses, huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.82,0:31:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.86,0:31:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NCan you put that to John?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.59,0:31:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is to our...\NJust normal resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.59,0:31:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it to John in the morning.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.68,0:31:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Attempt to transcend.\NAttempt to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.68,0:31:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Attempt to transcend.\NAddress this to John.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.58,0:31:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the guy who does our videos.\NWill you...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.58,0:31:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.58,0:31:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.19,0:31:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.02,0:32:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThis has to do with my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.02,0:32:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So much confusion.\NIt's a good job, and I think the company's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.01,0:32:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the job's integrous.\NBut it's just ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.42,0:32:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not...\NI feel like I'm not really contributing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.42,0:32:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just...\NI'm there eight hours a day, every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.42,0:32:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NMonday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.42,0:32:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NMonday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.42,0:32:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NMonday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.42,0:32:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NMonday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.42,0:32:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NMonday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.42,0:32:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NMonday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.42,0:32:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.58,0:32:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.81,0:32:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel like...\NAm I wasting my time?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.81,0:32:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the one good thing is it allows me to come here.\NI can come to all the talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.81,0:32:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best thing about it.\NBut am I just wasting my life in this job?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.81,0:32:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it depends on how you contextualize this work.\NHow do you contextualize this?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.81,0:32:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it being of service to others?\NIs it fulfilling the...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.97,0:32:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own potential?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.97,0:32:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.97,0:32:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.97,0:32:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.10,0:32:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.10,0:32:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.10,0:32:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.10,0:32:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.10,0:33:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it fulfilling your own potential?\NIs it just carrying forth responsibility towards yourself and your family for survival?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.10,0:33:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the best utilization of your skills?\NYou know, how you contextualize this value.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.10,0:33:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm not utilizing my potential, but I'm not sure what I should do, yet it's\Nintegrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.00,0:33:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI feel the job is still integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.00,0:33:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just ordinary.\NOh, the ego hates that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.12,0:33:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinary.\NI know there's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.71,0:33:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,plenty of ego there too\Nokay so it's because you contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.03,0:33:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it as being ordinary mundane\Npedestrians right
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.75,0:33:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have to learn how to recontextualize\Nits value
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.47,0:33:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it serves you and the world\Nit serves survival
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.74,0:33:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an expression of your\Nvalue of your life to others
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.60,0:33:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a valuable cog in the wheel\Nright
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.31,0:34:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nnot everybody has
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.69,0:34:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a life's work\Nsometimes people say
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.55,0:34:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born to do this\Nwe can't all be helicopter pilots
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.91,0:34:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nrescue swimmers
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.74,0:34:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the heroes aren't they\Nmost of us lead rather mundane lives
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.59,0:34:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nwe go to work every day
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.71,0:34:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and perform whatever skills we have\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.57,0:34:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you know\Nif you can intuit an alternate
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.89,0:34:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nwhen I'm saying through prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.58,0:34:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you say good lord\Nis there anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.04,0:34:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you would wish me to do\Nwhile I'm here
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.80,0:34:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with my time\Nand my energy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.48,0:34:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and my body\NI'd surrender my life to thee oh lord
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.98,0:34:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so you pray for God's guidance\Nin the 12 step group
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.54,0:34:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the 11th step\Nask God for direction
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.98,0:34:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nso you do
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.91,0:34:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you meditate\Nask God for direction
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.67,0:35:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you let it go\Nand nothing happens
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.63,0:35:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then one day\Nyou pick up a magazine cover
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.49,0:35:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and flash\Nthat's it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.97,0:35:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nyou just got it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.89,0:35:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not\Ncause and effect
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.59,0:35:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not volitional\Nit's not linear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.13,0:35:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when you let go\Nand forget about it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.07,0:35:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,trust that God will review\Nwhat
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.55,0:35:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what\NGod's will is for you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.01,0:35:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,see\Nand then forget about it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.81,0:35:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nwhen it comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.29,0:35:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and hits you in the head\Nlike a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.63,0:35:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,step down a hole\Noh that's it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.95,0:35:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,yep\Nthat's what I'm waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.81,0:35:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nmay not be so dramatic
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.85,0:35:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,those also serve\Nwho stand in wait
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.21,0:35:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.77,0:35:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.11,0:35:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.45,0:35:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nfor your patience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.65,0:35:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,steadfastness\NMary steadfastness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.44,0:35:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I\NI've sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.05,0:35:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,confused about something\Nactually two things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.43,0:35:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,one is\Never since I've been a child
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.53,0:35:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been very worried\Nabout the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.87,0:35:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm worried\Nabout the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.71,0:35:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,environment\Nthe environment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.73,0:36:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.41,0:36:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,looks pretty good\Nthe environment here
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,oh are you talking about\Nthe world's environment
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.72,0:36:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pollution\Nare you worried
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.40,0:36:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about the world\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.26,0:36:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Noh okay
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.46,0:36:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Neverybody's got to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.68,0:36:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,worry about something. So when I was a child, yeah, I tried to get my friends to take\Ncare of things and critters. Yes. And now I have a cable show where I interview
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.08,0:36:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,people to show what's wrong with the environment, what we could do. And I start\Nfeeling sort of, hmm, I don't know if that's the right way to do it. I'm really
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.02,0:36:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,confused about whether or not, quote, the environment needs help or what the\Nstatus of that is. Well, you see, you walk about in a state in which you see the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.60,0:36:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sacredness, holiness, deservingness, and divinity of all that exists, and you treat\Nit accordingly. And then what you do is a consequence of how you, how you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.57,0:37:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,understand it and grasp its significance. Yeah? You serve, you serve all of life\Nand all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.88,0:37:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Expressions. Yes? So would you say that the environment is in trouble? Our planet?\NYou can't be so general. You're asking, you know, is the planet in trouble? I don't know, I couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.36,0:37:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Is, uh, are there... The green stuff? Yeah. The animal stuff? Yeah. The oxygen? Yeah.\NEverybody does what they can to contribute to the best of their comprehension of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.66,0:37:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,their function in the world. I mean, I see myself automatically\Npicked up by the world. I mean, I see myself automatically picked up by the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.01,0:38:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,world. I see myself automatically picking up trash because I, I think, you know, it, it conceals the beauty of the world, you know? You find yourself automatically trying to serve the world as best you can just because that's your nature. It's not because of what you do, because of what you are, huh? Divers need a home, so you find yourself hanging in birdhouses. It's not to help the environment, that's, that's too much of a generality, you know?\NWell, how it fumes and cars and emissions and smokestacks and greenhouse effects?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.91,0:38:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the cause of all that? We are.\NAnd who is we? Me, yeah. No I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.36,0:38:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't. The totality of the population. We didn't have the problem\Nwhen I was born, there was only one-one billion people I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.46,0:38:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,1.5 billion. No, it's 6 billion. So the problem is not the planet\Nand the pollution. The problem is people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.88,0:38:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got so many people, that pollution is automatic. You can't do anything about...\Nthe forests and the pollution and the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.12,0:38:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When you've got a population running like this,\Nthe problem I see is this population.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.22,0:39:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the pollution of the ocean come from?\NNot people, lots of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.55,0:39:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Southern Asia, there is a cloud,\Na dust cloud of haze, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.94,0:39:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,three miles high.\NThree miles high.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.43,0:39:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because of the enormous population density.\NSo, to me, it's foolish to worry about the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.16,0:39:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,without first taking care of the population problem.\NI can't do anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.69,0:39:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I could.\NWell, you're going to put your effort somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.73,0:39:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NWhy not put it where it counts?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.87,0:39:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true.\NIf you don't want to be poor,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.26,0:39:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,have two kids instead of six.\NIt's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.36,0:39:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want pollution,\Ndon't ask so many people to live by the Ganges River.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.64,0:39:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I think the crux of it,\Nenvironmentalism,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.15,0:40:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is population sprawl.\NPopulation, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.31,0:40:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Population.\NYou know where it's people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.75,0:40:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to have a living,\Nso they have to go through the Amazon forest in Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.85,0:40:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to knock down the forest\Nbecause they have to have room for crops to raise the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.97,0:40:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the wild animals have to escape.\NBut is the problem tearing down the Amazon forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.35,0:40:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the main source of oxygen?\NThe Amazon forest is the source,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.87,0:40:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, 50% of the world's oxygen or something.\NDestroy it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.32,0:40:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So why do the people keep pushing in and destroying the forest?\NBecause there's so many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.14,0:40:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got good intention.\NWhy don't you put it to the source instead of the effect?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.36,0:40:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The environmental impact is the effect.\NIt's too late already.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.01,0:40:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NA hundred kids is going to make a lot of garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.62,0:41:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten times more than ten kids.\NAnd that's all it wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.90,0:41:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's my take on it.\NSounds logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.20,0:41:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The goodwill of your efforts is, you know, laudable,\Nbut I think futile.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.63,0:41:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,While you have a party for the environment,\Nthe bulldozers are relentless.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.97,0:41:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Giant iron monsters are running,\Ntearing down the Amazon forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.72,0:41:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the main source of oxygen on the planet right now.\NSo it would seem like education,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.07,0:41:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,education of responsibility.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.92,0:41:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's not responsible to have...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.16,0:41:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's responsible to have big kids when you can only afford two.\NSo to somehow raise the educational level.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.40,0:41:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does that is education.\NThey found that education does more than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.90,0:42:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Celtic, the Celtic tiger turnaround of Ireland\Nafter two centuries of extreme poverty was due to free education.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.00,0:42:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The higher the education, the less the overpopulation,\Nthe less the pollution, the less the environmental damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.30,0:42:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would start more to a central point of where it's all coming from.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.18,0:42:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you're bandaging things without getting to the fact\Nthat you've got a central infection.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.06,0:42:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Cure the infection, you don't have all these things to handle.\NIt's just more efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.27,0:42:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I see environmentalism running here, running there, running there.\NIn the meantime, the main faucet is still running, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.77,0:42:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just my take on it, but you asked me.\NWell, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.84,0:42:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for contributing.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.67,0:43:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.05,0:43:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NDr. Harkins?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.12,0:43:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.12,0:43:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.\NYou have said many times that only 0.4% of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.65,0:43:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,ever gets to 540 or unconditional love.\NYeah, true.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.65,0:43:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Given the world's population, though, that's 25 million people.\NGood, good math.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.65,0:43:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYet at 60 points higher, at 600, when you wrote Truth Versus Falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.16,0:43:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there were only six people there.\NWhat makes that 60 points higher?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.16,0:43:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.96,0:43:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what makes that 60 points of consciousness so extraordinarily hard\Nthat we start with 25 over one line and we only get six over another line?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To develop from 540 to 600?\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.02,0:43:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's unconditional.\NYou see, sainthood is at 55-55.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.02,0:43:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.09,0:43:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love is 540.\NThat itself is extremely unusual, as you know, to 0.4%.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.76,0:44:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That, to go from there, means practicing spiritual principles\Nwith no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.76,0:44:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No exception.\NHmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.18,0:44:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NIt means very strict allegiance to spiritual pathway, truth, and techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.66,0:44:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with no variation.\NAnd it means mounting dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.66,0:44:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, from 540, saintliness is around 570.\NThen, from there up, you encounter joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.99,0:44:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what joy is that, 580 or something?\NIs that ecstasy?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.94,0:44:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, from there, you, having let go of all the things that are deterrents,\Nyou go into a state of joy that is not the consequence of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.74,0:45:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the arising of an energy of the realization of the divinity of God\Nwithin as the source of one's existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.57,0:45:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This, as you continue to surrender to it, continues on up, gets more than that,\Nand it becomes ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.15,0:45:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstasy is over 580, 585, 590, 595.\NEcstasy is over 590.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.04,0:45:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstasy is very close.\NEcstasy is 595, 998, anyway, 598.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.77,0:45:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The ecstasy itself is extraordinary.\NIt cannot really be differentiated except by a sophisticated spiritual community
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.99,0:45:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from maybe spiritual mania or something.\NIn this book, the last book, I wrote how to differentiate spiritual states from pathologic states.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.50,0:46:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You go from joy, which is relatively impossible to function in the world,\Nand then you move to ecstasy, where it is impossible to function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.36,0:46:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go to ecstasy, you go into a state that I cannot hardly describe.\NIt is ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.87,0:46:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you're tireless.\NYou can dance forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.87,0:46:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance in front of the altar at midnight to the candlelight\Nin the ecstasy of the awareness of the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.00,0:46:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can do that tirelessly, hour after hour.\NYou don't have to eat anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.67,0:46:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to drink anything.\NYou don't dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.18,0:46:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You are danced by the ecstasy.\NCertain symbols from ancient India come to your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.46,0:47:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity and its expression.\NIn the Hindu language and religion, culture has certain expressions and styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.68,0:47:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That state, you can become addicted to it.\NThe ecstasy is so ecstatic that the thought of existing without it is not even thinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.20,0:47:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then comes the knowingness in that extremely high state.\NThis, too, must be surrendered to the ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.04,0:47:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See, O Lord.\NAnd the ecstasy is surrendered to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.88,0:47:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you come into the state of profound and infinite peace and bliss.\NAbsolutely still, exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.60,0:48:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to eat, drink, breathe, or nothing.\NWhether the body survives or not is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.15,0:48:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're merely the witness.\NSat-cittananda.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.46,0:48:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,State of infinite bliss.\NThe opportunity to leave, in fact, almost a beckoning to leave, is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.04,0:48:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people leave there.\NA few remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.92,0:48:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's very few, over 600, because of karmic propensity,\Nbecause of, I wouldn't say desire to leave, but the option to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.16,0:48:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I think there is.\NI forget how many.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.88,0:48:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There were six.\NYes, that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.88,0:48:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, when you wrote your first book, there were 12 over 700.\NBut they leave, they leave, they leave, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.88,0:49:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they only stay in that state for a certain length of time.\NAnd there's been considerable periods of time when nobody over 600 was on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.20,0:49:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, six is quite a few.\NVery often annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.42,0:49:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Centuries go by with not a single enlightened sage.\NAnd you see how rare they are throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.20,0:49:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take all the greatest sages of history,\Nput them all together over a time track, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.20,0:49:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we always thought there were a lot more.\NThey were just hidden somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.26,0:49:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they send off such an energy that they don't just remain suddenly hidden in a cave.\NSomehow it radiates out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.55,0:49:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.91,0:49:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy is surrendered to ecstasy.\NAnd then the ecstasy is surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.91,0:49:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know for what.\NAnd then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.91,0:50:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is the peace beyond all understanding.\NThe peace of God, that's 600, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.39,0:50:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,On the last four charts that you showed,\Nit seemed to me like the consciousness on the left side was about 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.85,0:50:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and on the right side was about 290.\NWhich means that the right side becomes another bunch of shoulds,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.36,0:50:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which then become limitations.\NAnd it seems to me like you need to be neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.56,0:50:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,like the self-forgiveness.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.56,0:50:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you talking about attractions and aversions?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.56,0:50:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NSo it seems to me even on the right side of the chart,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.56,0:50:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to be neutral to forgiving yourself or not forgiving yourself.\NYeah, it's a very high state.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.68,0:50:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.45,0:50:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing to forgive.\NThere is no decision to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.45,0:50:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are is perfect.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.45,0:50:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for you.\NGod bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.45,0:51:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.72,0:51:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NLet me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.19,0:51:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who writes, beats up a book like this deserves a question.\NThis is the raggedy one I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.19,0:51:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's new.\NThank you for the compliment, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.25,0:51:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.25,0:51:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the main thing is one time you said that\Ntruth is the highest expression of divinity on this plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.53,0:51:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not necessarily.\NIt's only one of the aspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.92,0:51:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the highest?\NYou can't say, see that's projecting the linear to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.90,0:52:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is grace, there is love, there is divine order, harmony, infinite mercy, compassion,\Ninfinite love.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.32,0:52:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really say that one is higher than the other.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.32,0:52:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In a certain extent, they're all the same.\NDifferent expressions of the same energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.32,0:52:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This way it looks like love, this way it looks like truth, this way it looks like compassion,\Nthis way it looks like forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.32,0:52:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, this way it's mercy.\NBut it's only the same way of being, you know, type of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.37,0:52:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One is not really higher than the other.\NYou can choose the option to try to approach enlightenment via one pathway or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.88,0:52:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is more individual proclivity.\NMany people are more heart people.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.62,0:52:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people would maybe go through the intellect and become Zen,\Nyou know, go for Zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.62,0:53:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Some would go through selfless service.\NSo the various yogas, selfless service, meditation, bhakti yoga,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.62,0:53:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,would be sort of personal proclivity, you know what I'm saying?\NAnd truth is always relative to the absolute?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.61,0:53:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's expression in this plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.47,0:53:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Is relative to the absolute.\NIs relative, you know, relative to the absolute, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.47,0:53:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSee a diamond, this way it looks that way, this way it looks this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.54,0:53:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's all the same diamond, what do you call it?\NLove, compassion, mercy, omnipotence, omniscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.31,0:53:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just different facets of the diamond, you know.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.24,0:53:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NVery nice to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.24,0:53:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,On the videos you've mentioned several times about the 91st Psalm.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.24,0:53:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So I brought one.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.24,0:54:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from the internet and you probably could link to it.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.24,0:54:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I brought one just in case you wanted to make a comment.\NI can link on your website.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.24,0:54:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you so much.\NAnd it's a little bit crumpled from the airplane and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.24,0:54:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NQuite a bit crumpled.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.24,0:54:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of the questions that I had, you've already answered.\NSo every time I have a question at home, I watch a video and the answer comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.24,0:54:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo I have no questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.24,0:54:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's very good for you.\NI bet every, I'm constantly surrendering and talking to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.24,0:54:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NAnd I had some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.24,0:54:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI had a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.24,0:54:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI had a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.24,0:54:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.24,0:54:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.24,0:54:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.24,0:54:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.24,0:54:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.24,0:54:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI had some hopes, but then I surrendered them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.54,0:54:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I had hopes of finding a husband, and then after eight years, I had to, I think that\Neverybody I met was undoing past karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.56,0:55:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a lot of .\NSo again, I surrender even wanting a husband, but it would be very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.74,0:55:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NI would.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.74,0:55:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, then we'll get you one.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.74,0:55:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.74,0:55:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she should have what she wants.\NThe sweet, adorable lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.74,0:55:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, sweet, adorable ladies.\NWhere are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.74,0:55:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You better get them while you can.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.74,0:55:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Susan.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.74,0:55:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know she'll find them.\NMmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.74,0:55:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.74,0:55:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of them.\NBoth of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.74,0:55:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NMy name is Louis.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.61,0:55:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for being available to us after your, this incredible work and all\Nthe reading I have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.61,0:55:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredible research.\NI'm very impressed about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.61,0:55:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been a follower and the leader of spiritual group in the past.\NIn where?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.61,0:56:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the spiritual groups.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.25,0:56:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the spiritual groups have been very helpful to me.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.25,0:56:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.25,0:56:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.44,0:56:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\Nin a way of a spiritual group, okay? It was Eckengard, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.76,0:56:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Eckengard. Yes.\NOh, yeah, yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.12,0:56:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My question, I have two or three questions. Can, when we have faith in a spiritual leader,\Nand I had the experience of grace of God many years ago, and I will never forget about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.30,0:56:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Can, do you understand that? Yes?\NShe'll tell me what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.42,0:56:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNot Jackson. She tells me what people are saying all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.83,0:57:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that our faith could only lead us to this sense of grace of God and not the leader?\NCan we project the faith? Is it based on the grace of God or is it based on the leader of the group?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.59,0:57:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he's asking.\NIt's the grace of God. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.70,0:57:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you karmically\Nembody
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.54,0:57:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the level that you're at, will attract or be attracted to a teacher of that level, see?\NBut does my faith could make me feel the grace of God even if that leader could be not?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.78,0:57:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, if the leader is not sufficient for you, then you'll be called away by another leader.\NYes. Somebody will say, you know, so-and-so and, you know, calibrate it and see where it's at, and
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.14,0:57:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then you go through. Yes.\NI'm a little disillusion, but, in the end. I remember somebody saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.28,0:57:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, he's a great teacher, except he has no energy around the heart. Bang.\NAnd when we are followers, and I was a leader in my area, so are we limited to the level
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.75,0:58:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness, of the group, or we can transcend this level?\NYou'll go to it. You'll go in accord of what you're attracted to and if you evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.19,0:58:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond it, you'll lose your interest and find something more exciting and more appropriate, yeah.\NSo staying could be a drag on my spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.19,0:58:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying might be a drag on that spiritual effort to transcend.\NYes, that's true. That's true?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.25,0:58:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you know, when it's time to change, somehow it comes to you, it's time to change.\NOkay, even if I'm responsible with some people in my area, because I feel a bit responsible also, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.57,0:58:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take a little consultation to resolve what you're talking about.\NYou're talking about multiple issues now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.57,0:58:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Appropriateness of the teacher, the appropriateness of the group, and the appropriateness of your role, you know what I'm saying?\NIt's a little complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.57,0:59:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay, thank you. You answered most of my questions.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.15,0:59:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much again.\NWhen it's time to move on, it sort of comes in some way to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.15,0:59:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.40,0:59:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else begins to click.\NYeah, he got involved with an Eckhart group, now he's lucky to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.56,0:59:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So nice to be here.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.13,0:59:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering about praying for the dying. Is that a good practice? Or would it be helpful?\NYou know the admonition, pray ceaselessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.92,0:59:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just pray all the time for everyone?\NIt is advantageous, we have permission to ask this, it is advantageous to pray for the dying, resist. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.99,1:00:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking because my mother seems to be in that process, and I don't know what, I don't really know how to pray.\NI'm used to praying for myself, you know, ask God for help for this and that, but not for other people, because I feel like I'm interfering.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.99,1:00:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I don't know...\NYou're butting into their karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.99,1:00:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Like, how do I know what...\NWell, you ask for the highest good for this person and hold them alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.99,1:00:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we did when we did the Ohms, right?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.99,1:00:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's the highest good for these people.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.99,1:00:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe to crash in despair and say, dear God, I ask you, only you, no one else can, you know, in despair.\NIt's called hitting bottom. So many people find God through hitting bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.34,1:00:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take a typhoon, a hurricane, starvation, and being shot. Just as your body falls over, you got it. So who knows, huh?\NWell, I found on the river doing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.68,1:00:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I found on the river doing that, that beautiful Ohm prayer that I was holding in mind these people crying for help.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.68,1:01:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And could I have a different visualization be more beneficial? I mean, what could I...in my mind, I had an image of...\NYou're trying to control it. Just be who you are with it. Your intention is to help these people and pray for them. That's good enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.68,1:01:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But...\NLet God worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.28,1:01:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI can see you saying thank you to the assistant. She didn't pray very good that time, did she?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.88,1:01:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you think she's got a scoreboard?\NYour intention is the goodwill to express unconditional love towards the people. That's sufficient. The intention is what does it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.36,1:01:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.36,1:01:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be all right to use the...to do the Ohm? Because I thought it was wonderful.\NYou can do whatever you like. You can stand on your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.87,1:01:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, cranking a prayer wheel calibrates at 540.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.87,1:01:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's the intention. It's not the mechanicalness. It's just a tin thing with things written on it.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.87,1:01:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intention.\NThe intention. You know, the intention of genuine reflection. The intention of prayerful hand-plast.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.28,1:02:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is 540. So the intention of however you pray is sufficient. Okay?\NAnd it seems like prayer helps...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.28,1:02:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop questioning and doubting about it. Just stop and do it at the end.\NDon't make it complicated. You're making it complicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.53,1:02:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou better see a priest. He'll tell you how to pray.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.60,1:02:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. Let's see.\NI'm on page 342 here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.60,1:02:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called the prayer for the sick and dying. I can get you any prayer book. Look it up.\NIt's called prayer book. Prayers for the sick and dying. Prayers for the deceased.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.11,1:02:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good place to start.\NTake any of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.43,1:02:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you get a prayer book?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.43,1:02:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got it listed. Prayers for the sick and dying. Prayers for certain people in surgery. Prayers for people in pain.\NThey've got prayers for specific things. So have a professional set up a prayer for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.58,1:03:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it. One up for a dollar and a half. Twenty-two bucks.\NI'll give you twenty-two bucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.76,1:03:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a prayer book.\NOkay. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.14,1:03:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Unity should help you too. I mean, you know, Unity has got prayer books for all that stuff. Don't you have a minister around you?\NI don't. I've never gone to church.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.14,1:03:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This lady needs a minister. Hello.\NA soul that needs rescuing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.14,1:03:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't go to church.\NI'm selling her for a dollar. Anybody can have her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.14,1:03:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's prayer groups. Like Unity has a prayer group.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.14,1:03:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You need a prayer book.\NThere's other denominations.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.14,1:03:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You need a prayer book. Just an ordinary prayer book.\NAnd if you don't know how to pray for them, then you can have a prayer group.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.14,1:03:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'll tell you how. It's easy.\NPray book. So, you know, there's other...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.14,1:03:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinary prayer book. Okay?\NWho can?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.24,1:03:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's people that will pray for your mother.\NStop in the nearest hotel and look in the drawer next to the bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.61,1:03:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you, Sarah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.61,1:04:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She's sweet.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.98,1:04:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question about surrendering.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.98,1:04:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like I have selective surrendering.\NSome things go away and stay away, and some seem to come back repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.04,1:04:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So maybe...\NRepeat that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.84,1:04:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When I surrender some things, they seem to go away and stay away, but others seem to come back over and over.\NOthers come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.84,1:04:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So I was hoping...\NYou didn't surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.84,1:04:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not good enough.\NWhen you surrender, it doesn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.84,1:04:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,True. So maybe you can go over the mechanics of surrendering.\NI think I should go over the mechanics of surrendering one more time because some of these things keep coming back.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.84,1:04:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have to do it repeatedly.\NDear God, I ask you to help me let go my attachment to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.32,1:04:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what the payoff you're getting from clinging to it or what the aversion is to letting it go.\NYou've got to look deeper within yourself to see what the obstruction is, the resistance is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.32,1:05:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things require repeated surrendering, repeated surrendering because it's a big stack.\NIt's a big stack.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.32,1:05:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a short stack of short duration, you can let it go with a few surrenders.\NYou can do it in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.32,1:05:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it's a big one, a big one, you may have to do it over and over again and ask for God's help each time.\NThen decide what is the quality of that which you're attached to.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.48,1:05:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's the thing.\NIt's the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.48,1:05:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the thing.\NIt's the juice you're getting out of your attachment to the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.48,1:05:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you're not willing to surrender, including feeling guilty that you haven't surrendered it.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.94,1:05:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to look at the payouts on both sides.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.51,1:05:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things require persistence.\NJust be persistent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.51,1:05:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever got a spiritual counselor?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.24,1:06:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the trouble with today's world.\NWhen we have a spiritual counselor, people really benefit from a spiritual counselor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.24,1:06:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They benefit from a spiritual confidant.\NSomeone with whom to bounce back things.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.84,1:06:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody really, in my view, needs a mentor.\NEverybody really needs a confidant, a confessor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.84,1:06:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not Catholic, become one and go to confession.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.07,1:06:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody needs sort of a feedback.\NIn the 12-step groups, everybody has a sponsor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.07,1:06:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody does it on their own.\NEverybody shares what they're working through.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.48,1:06:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they get feedback from the older, wiser.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.87,1:06:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The mentor is sadly lacking in today's society.\NEverybody needs a mentor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.92,1:06:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a trusted older friend, confidant.\NSomebody who you know has your best interest at heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.04,1:07:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NAnd you can share their wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.12,1:07:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That helps you grow.\NIt's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.67,1:07:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.08,1:07:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThe bartender used to serve that assumption, but they...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.74,1:07:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's against the union rules now.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.74,1:07:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if he gives you advice and you take it and it doesn't work, you can sue the bartender.\NSo bartenders are no longer allowed to be spiritual counselors.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.09,1:07:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You used to be a bartender.\NI was a bartender.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.09,1:07:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I frankly did give out the best advice I could.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.41,1:07:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because here's a fellow human being in trouble asking you, you know, for...\NFeedback.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.41,1:07:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're just an ordinary human, you feel for the, you know...\NNot through sympathy, but through empathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.41,1:07:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it must feel like to have your wife leave you and get fired and all that\Nall on the same day, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.31,1:08:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NHi, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.59,1:08:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.59,1:08:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, I was recently listening to a lecture, a recorded lecture of the workshop, Intention.\NAnd...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.59,1:08:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNear the beginning, you said something to the effect that you are going to just tell
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.97,1:08:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,us what is going on.\NWhat you're going to do in the workshop is you're going to just tell us what's going
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.97,1:08:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on in the world, consciousness with the ego.\NAnd all you ask us to do is just pay attention and notice it, and that you don't want us
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.20,1:08:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to think about it.\NI'm helping to...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.26,1:08:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you can help me understand that without thinking about it.\NNo, just go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.12,1:08:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that in the video, Power of the Intention, that you told them that all you wanted them\Nto do is sit back and listen and absorb it and not really think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.12,1:08:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.12,1:09:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhat did you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.12,1:09:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.12,1:09:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I needed help.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.12,1:09:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.12,1:09:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.48,1:09:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.48,1:09:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.\NThis is why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.48,1:09:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what.\NYou heard it, that what you heard is imprinted as a frequency vibration in your aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.96,1:09:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When you need to know it, it speaks forth to you from within.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.99,1:09:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not from memory, because that's either aura or duality.\NIt's like a knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.04,1:09:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like, oh, you know what to do.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.13,1:09:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NDon't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.80,1:10:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even a little bit.\NDon't think about thinking about it. No, he got it in his heart. He's conscious of the realization.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.40,1:10:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just here to say, you know, I love what you do and I love who you are\Nand I don't have a question and I want to cast a vote. I vote for you to, next year,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.48,1:10:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when you do this six times instead of doing half a day, to do a full day. That's my vote.\NHis suggestion would serve the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.52,1:10:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,His suggestion would serve the highest good.\NAll right, we'll compromise. I'll talk for in the morning, but all afternoon will be spent with the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.88,1:11:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,group, conversation, being with each other, mingling, sharing, discussing, if we can arrange it.\NThanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.20,1:11:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask if it\Nserved the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.64,1:11:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It serves my highest good.\NIt serves my highest good, to agree.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.91,1:11:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.66,1:11:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you were going to get off your feet.\NYeah. Well, I don't know. I'm always afraid. I'm afraid I'm being repetitious, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.79,1:11:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm repeating many of the same things again. I think other, you know, yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.49,1:11:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NDid you hear what she said?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.93,1:11:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender.\NSurrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.60,1:11:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't surrender unless I resist, so I got something to surrender.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.92,1:12:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My issue is some kind of a reaction that I have if I'm in, let's say, a little group.\NIt could be a spiritual group and somebody asks a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.32,1:12:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is, it's been answered a lot.\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.01,1:12:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.\Nor repeated a lot of other times I'm gonna have to listen to the long answer
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.11,1:12:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I tend to get up and walk out of the room or just feel great impatience when\NI also feel that with other drivers sometimes especially when the driver
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.53,1:12:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,honks at me and I haven't done much I keep observing this but I keep reacting\Nimpatience you're talking about yeah yeah yeah well impatience is what
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.37,1:13:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,willfulness uncurbed willfulness uh-huh there's a child then yeah what went on\Nabout that with you as a child with your mother or your father did you just keep
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.08,1:13:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,hollering and yelling to get your way what went on no I think I had a hard\Ntime doing certain things I had a hard time doing it right so I
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.43,1:13:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I\Nwas criticized if you didn't get your way yeah so impatience if you didn't do it
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.18,1:13:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,right if you didn't do it right yeah but I don't see these people aren't doing it\Nright with the questions they ask it's the insensitive so you get impatient
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.54,1:13:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about being bored is that right that's right well what is boredom about\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.70,1:14:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it about boredom it must be about juicing the ego resisting boredom\Nyeah I resist boredom yeah you're resisting boredom yes oh who is it this
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.60,1:14:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,board what is it this board it's really that leading edge of the ego yeah the\Nleading edge yeah yeah mm-hmm the leading edge is reporting to you what it
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.75,1:14:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks is happening that's not what happening it's reporting to you what's\Nit's not reporting you what's happening that's why you get bored with it I think
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.95,1:14:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to learn to quit thinking\Nunderneath the thinginess is an infinite silence right this instant I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.66,1:15:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,tuned into the silence nothing at all is happening do you like that no TV on no\Ndog barking no nothing going on yes what happens with that in that space basically
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.66,1:15:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's happening.\NNothing's happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.48,1:15:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's peaceful and quiet.\NIs that okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.48,1:15:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOkay, live there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.48,1:15:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay there.\NGet what that space is and carry it with you as that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.34,1:15:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think that peace and silence is out there, it's within you.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.78,1:15:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSee, the silence is just underneath the thinkingness and the amusement service.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.82,1:15:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay within that.\NAnd whatever goes on is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.35,1:15:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They're killing each other out there and you say, yeah, uh-huh.\NAnd the water's getting here, right, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.86,1:16:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the bullets are flying.\NYou say, yeah, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.06,1:16:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.34,1:16:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so learn how to say so.\NBecause that negates the value of thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.73,1:16:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So?\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.73,1:16:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI'm going to kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.73,1:16:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So?\NWhat do you want me to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.37,1:16:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the cops?\NCall the cops or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.37,1:16:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NJust say so to whatever conversation is going on, in or out, and live in the silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.56,1:16:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason why people say it doesn't bother me is I haven't in this life paid any attention\Nto it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.28,1:16:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You look interested, but you don't have any investment in it.\NYou make appropriate social responses, you're going to kill yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.67,1:17:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NWhy is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.41,1:17:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NYou see, people try to jerk you around and play you with their drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.94,1:17:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When you refuse the drama game, you can live in a peaceful silence and the whole thing's\Namusing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.94,1:17:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of being impatient and driven, you know, be like the witness of it.\NYou're just the witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.94,1:17:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,From the silence, you witness it all.\NThe birds come, the birds nest, spring comes, fall comes, wars come, peace comes, the parades
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.74,1:17:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,go by.\NThey pile up the caskets.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.03,1:17:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.42,1:17:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's good.\NStick with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.28,1:17:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stick with what I'm telling you.\NDon't try and elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.28,1:17:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.28,1:17:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stay with what I said to you.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.28,1:17:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.28,1:17:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They come, they go.\NThe seas rise, the seas fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.41,1:17:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The birds fly, the birds fall.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.41,1:17:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NHmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.41,1:18:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NThis morning you talked about the surest way to kill a sunset is for people to talk
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.21,1:18:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.21,1:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Um.\NWhat's the best way to kill a sunset?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.78,1:18:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As time goes on, I tend, I'm tending to see beauty in just about everything.\NAs time goes on what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.78,1:18:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen the beauty in everything.\NYeah, you see the beauty, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.78,1:18:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd then the tendency of people is to, is to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.78,1:18:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat's, uh, I'm finding annoying.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.78,1:18:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's, I'm wondering how that gets resolved.\NUm, it doesn't really.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.78,1:18:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you today, I think it's, I'm not telling you how it's going to be resolved.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.78,1:18:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI just, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.78,1:18:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.78,1:18:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.78,1:18:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NBut I'm trying to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.78,1:19:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that gets resolved? It doesn't really. I told you today, in the great cathedrals of the world,\Nand I told you if I had to be reborn, I'd like to be a janitor in Shark Cathedral. That would
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.03,1:19:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,be the most exquisite possible job, you know what I'm saying? At midnight, nobody's there.\NThere's yourself in the entire cathedral. Yeah, I've done that, and that sends you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.32,1:19:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,into ecstasy, and there's nobody in the cathedral except yourself, and you go right into ecstasy,\Ntireless, infinite ecstasy. Yeah, so you can look around the noise that's being made. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.11,1:19:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, we were there a couple years ago, and you look around the nuisance,\Nas I say, the same thing happened in front of the Statue of Lincoln in Washington, D.C. there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.50,1:20:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredibly impressive. Just what it is stands out to you. It's so stunning,\Nand you wonder how people can be even thinking of what they're talking about, you know? So you
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.23,1:20:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,look beyond it, okay? Beyond it. Okay, thank you. Go back at midnight.\NThe Church of the Red Rocks, I used to do that. The music would go all night long,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.30,1:20:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the candles were on, and nobody was there. Yes, okay, yeah, I'm sure they're there.\NFrom a personal point of view, there are days, for example, when I feel as an individual that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.94,1:20:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is going perfectly well. You know, you're floating down the river. You're not trying\Nto swim upstream, you hear some music on the radio, it's beautiful, or you see the sunset
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.98,1:21:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,without comment, but there are also days when that's not true, so would you perhaps help\Nexplain, on days which that's not true, am I getting in my own way, is it something...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.22,1:21:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And the days when it's not true, it's just something coming up that you need to process,\Nand it's calling for attention, this aggravates me, or this bothers me, or I feel attached
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.74,1:21:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to this, I have an aversion to that, it just brings up what you need to work on, see sometimes\Nyou get above your karma, and everything's peaceful and nice, and now you've used up
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.94,1:21:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,your good karma, and now the next stack is coming up for recognition, you're temporarily\Nabove it, but it isn't done yet, so the self wants to see you continuously progress, so
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.68,1:21:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives\Nyou a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.12,1:21:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to\Nprogress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.12,1:21:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives\Nyou a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.12,1:21:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress,\Nand it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.12,1:21:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you\Na chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.12,1:21:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and it gives you a chance to progress, and\Nhave to be more alert not to get in your own way
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.08,1:21:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or not let those obstacles come up\Nthat you were talking about this morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.56,1:21:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when you say the disturbance comes up,\Nyou have to look at what is the disturbance
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.30,1:22:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and why the disturbance is going on,\Nand you work on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.22,1:22:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that will disappear,\Nand life will be happy and cheerful and chipper,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.66,1:22:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can sing songs,\Nand then the next thing will come up.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.90,1:22:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right.\NIt's okay. It's a long process.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.58,1:22:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a growth process.\NIt's a process.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.36,1:22:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you very much.\NI appreciate so much what you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.58,1:22:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.37,1:22:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a lifelong process.\NWhen it gets to be so nice like that, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.82,1:22:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,why didn't it stay that way?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.70,1:22:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,May I ask one quick question before my main question?\NBefore what?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.95,1:22:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The main question.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.67,1:22:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIn your 1996 video, Power Versus Force,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.58,1:22:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you had this blonde that helped you.\NCan you teach me how to enter into her field
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.08,1:22:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and do anything I'm going to have to do to get out of what?\NHe had a blonde in that video.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.22,1:23:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHe wants to know how to enter into her field.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.50,1:23:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you mean by enter into her field.\NHow about a telephone number or a...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.30,1:23:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even know who he's talking about.\NI don't see her in the audience here.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.90,1:23:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what is your real question?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.74,1:23:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.95,1:23:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm involved in three areas of research and practice now.\NOne is using the mind mirror to look at brain waves patterns.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.46,1:23:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Another is using genograms for family constellation work.\NAnd the third is I'm a Western and Vedic astrologer
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.31,1:23:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to integrate the two disciplines into a higher astrology.\NIn your book, Truth and Falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.73,1:23:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you calibrated astrology, I think, between 205 and 410,\Nand is it possible to create a higher astrology?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.05,1:24:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There are various levels of astrology.\NWhen people talk about astrology,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.93,1:24:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not talking about just one thing.\NThere's the astrology in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.17,1:24:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrates the lowest sort of pop astrology.\NThen there's astrology based on more ancient wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.36,1:24:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which really is going beyond astrology,\Nlooking at contextual understandings.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.80,1:24:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a linear causality anymore.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.42,1:24:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that when I said that the consciousness level of mankind\Nwent from 190 to 205,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.25,1:24:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that was about at the time the harmonic concordance,\Nbut not caused by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.89,1:24:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, in November of what was it,\N203, we were in San Francisco,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.57,1:24:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it went from 205 to 207.\NThat was again at the time of,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.89,1:24:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I'm using the correct terminology,\Nharmonic concordance.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.75,1:24:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo aligned with that, at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.01,1:25:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because if the universe is doing this,\Nthen these things are both moving as a consequence of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.35,1:25:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,not because this is causing this.\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.71,1:25:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The understanding and the astrological sign\Nare appearing because they are both being swung this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.65,1:25:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NThis is not causing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.43,1:25:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is concomitant.\NVery often the ego confuses concomitant with causal.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.81,1:25:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to present astrology\Nin a new context so it has a higher calibration?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.21,1:25:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI think it would be significance and meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.68,1:25:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The limitation of astrology as I see it is causality.\NYou lost your job because the moon is going over your backyard.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.33,1:25:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NThat's causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.66,1:25:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That constellation is not causing anything here at all.\NSo if you move beyond duality,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.44,1:26:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you could move it to a higher...\NAstrology could work out as,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.38,1:26:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, a concordance in which you pick up rhythms\Nwhich are the consequence of greater rhythms,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.78,1:26:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or the consequence of even greater rhythms.\NEventually you reach the mind of God
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.56,1:26:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,who will tell you to forget about astrology.\NWhat about brain wave patterns?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.00,1:26:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting, yes.\NIs it worthwhile to pursue?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.26,1:26:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on what context.\NLooking at brain wave patterns of people at different disciplines
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.80,1:26:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and different levels.\NAnd different accomplishments and different contributions?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.94,1:26:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt would be some kind of research.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.60,1:26:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the purpose would be.\NTo find out different skills.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.27,1:26:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole area of brain research\Nis emerging rather rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.15,1:26:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd have to know more about it.\NI've lost track of where it's at right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.16,1:27:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah, it takes this moment to express my deepest love
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.62,1:27:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and gratitude to God and to God's teachings.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.50,1:27:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you.\NBecause in the last few months, my life has changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.50,1:27:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two questions.\NThe first question is about the calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.08,1:27:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on the transcendental meditations.\NTranscendental meditations?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.05,1:27:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,TM.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.25,1:27:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, yes.\NSo it is very low.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.57,1:27:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 200, yeah.\NI read some of their material.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.19,1:27:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They are practicing, you know, promote peace.\NAnd...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.65,1:27:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the question?\NThe question is, why is the TM calibrated so low?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.14,1:27:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by so low?\NWhat is the number?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.18,1:28:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like 200-something on your slide.\NIt's over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.98,1:28:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,200 is...\NTruth is 200 or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.80,1:28:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.60,1:28:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't created by the Buddha.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.19,1:28:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah, in my mind, I thought it should be higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.02,1:28:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the second question is about the jaya,\Nthe jaya hypothesis, is this?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.56,1:28:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jaya hypothesis?\NYes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.56,1:28:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NCan you...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.56,1:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth is a living organism.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.56,1:28:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you share some light on this?\NIt calibrates as negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.56,1:28:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear it breathing...\NIs that a fantasy or a reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.87,1:28:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is jaya a living organism?\NMy understanding is that it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.44,1:28:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it calibrate?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.44,1:28:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming to you to ask for your calibration.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.44,1:28:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.04,1:28:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.46,1:28:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.46,1:28:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.46,1:28:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.46,1:28:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.46,1:28:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.46,1:29:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give me theting of what you're calibrating?\NOh, you want me to calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.46,1:29:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.\NWe have permission to calibrate the concept of your...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.96,1:29:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permitted to calibrate the concept of yours.\NNo?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.98,1:29:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does that mean?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.04,1:29:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It means we gotta know.\NWe cannot calibrate it?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.54,1:29:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't calibrate it right now.\NWe've gotta know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.04,1:29:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a concept.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.39,1:29:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it, what difference does it make you is what I wanna know?\NYeah, I come from the science background.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.39,1:29:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah, but then recently after studying your teachings, I feel like I made the transition to the nonlinear domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.39,1:29:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd because of this, I see that there was a merging between science and spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.39,1:29:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I see the Gaia hypothesis actually bring an opportunity to this endeavor.\NHe feels that the Gaia...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.38,1:29:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gaia is a living single organism, is the concept, correct?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.64,1:30:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Gaia means that all that exists as the Earth is one single unit. Is that true?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.37,1:30:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have the same karma as the bacteria, the octopus, the snake, the fish, the killer, the bandit, the murderer?\NDo you share the same karma with all of them? Are you one with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.81,1:30:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThen by your own definition, you are. They'll have to serve you where you are now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.84,1:30:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you caused all that disaster?\NIn New Orleans, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.36,1:30:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we will learn something from it.\NBecause we learned something from it?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.25,1:30:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.96,1:30:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the value of holding the concept of Gaia? What is the value of it?\NYeah, my...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.95,1:31:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As a scientist, you know?\NYes. Personally, I feel like the science is hitting a wall, and it's convergence of these two domains may bring a new consciousness to our being.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.17,1:31:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a working concept.\NI think it's a useful concept, yes. Whether it's a self-existent reality or something else, but it certainly is a useful concept. You treat the whole thing as if it's one. That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.80,1:31:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it bring more unity consciousness by advocating this?\NWe don't know. We don't know if it's going to bring unity.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.24,1:31:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you're free to hold your concept about what the world is and what it means and what its significance is, you know.\NYeah, it depends on age, sophistication, education, many things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.20,1:31:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.20,1:31:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't calibrate it so we can't go any further with it. We've got to know that...\NIt's useful to him. It's useful to him right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.66,1:31:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it's useful to you...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.20,1:32:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.13,1:32:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't heard that concept in a while.\NThe Gaia?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.13,1:32:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Mm-hmm. Yeah.\NHi. You have described the experience energetically of the high 500s.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.78,1:32:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And specifically the energy as it travels up the spine.\NYeah. Kind of leaning in. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.78,1:32:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As this intense, exquisite experience.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.78,1:32:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it always present in that way in the high 500s?\NNothing is always anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.84,1:32:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NCharacteristically, that's how it is. That's how experienced it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.84,1:32:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NVery exquisite, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.84,1:32:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And specifically up the spinal column like that?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.91,1:32:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was experientially. It flowed up the back.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.91,1:33:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And into the brain.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.91,1:33:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you thought of the left side of the brain, it poured into the left side of the brain.\NIf you thought of the right side of the brain, it poured into the right side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.91,1:33:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it came down and began to go out into the world.\NMm-hmm. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.20,1:33:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd if you shut your eyes, it got even more intense.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.20,1:33:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NI'm trying to just formulate another question.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.85,1:33:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there are times when I feel...\NI remember as a kid watching Sylvester the Cat, I think, in cartoons.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.52,1:33:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And his tail would go into the outlet and he would fry with electricity.\NDo you need me to repeat it? No?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.00,1:33:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she'll have to tell me what to say.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.09,1:33:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are times when I experience that.\NAnd I'm trying to understand is that...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.22,1:34:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a resistance?\NYou mean like an energy surge is what you feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.76,1:34:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.76,1:34:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really a surge.\NMore just like a huge overload.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.76,1:34:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,More.\NAnd trying to understand is it resistance?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.76,1:34:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be, yeah.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.76,1:34:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat happens if you just continuously surrender to it and let it be whatever it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.63,1:34:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then it seems to spread out more and dissipate.\NI mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.20,1:34:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, like I'll need to lay down on the floor sometimes.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.20,1:34:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes after 10 or 15 minutes of that...\NYou just surrender to it no matter what form or expression it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.06,1:34:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNo, that's the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.09,1:34:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYou know, and you ask God for, you know, understanding and revelation of its meaning and significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.38,1:35:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things, I've found, just don't resist them.\NBecause one usually evolves into something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.11,1:35:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou don't have to worry about it, because it's gonna stay anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.11,1:35:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.11,1:35:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's transitional, so don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.11,1:35:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.73,1:35:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.92,1:35:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I work in a hospital, and I'm exposed, I guess.\NI'm surrounded by viruses and bacteria, and they calibrated a one.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.56,1:35:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.\NWell, no, there just seems to be a lot of attention within the healthcare system.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.64,1:35:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.64,1:35:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.64,1:35:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.64,1:35:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.64,1:35:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.64,1:35:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.87,1:35:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.87,1:35:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd I'm also within the health system that I'm...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.16,1:35:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In a hospital?\NIn a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.16,1:35:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You're working in a hospital, is that what you're saying?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.16,1:35:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, what is the question?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.16,1:35:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And there seems to be a lot of attention, if a virus and bacteria calibrated a one...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.16,1:35:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There seems to be a lot of attention paid to something that calibrates at a one.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.32,1:36:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're giving it a lot of power, it seems.\NDoes it have that much power, or are we just giving it the power?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.32,1:36:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it doesn't have power.\NIt doesn't have power.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.32,1:36:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NSo, pneumonia isn't real?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.64,1:36:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can...\NYou can...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.64,1:36:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You...\Nusing force and power. And it's not the bacteria, it's the body's reaction to it, yeah? You're
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.78,1:36:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,confusing power and force. Bin Laden calibrates at 20, and 9-11 is the consequence. So you\Nsee what I'm saying? That which is by virtue of its form is destructive, not by virtue
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.91,1:36:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of its power.\NSo just by, like it calibrates at a 1. So just being at a 1.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.46,1:36:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bacteria are at a 1 as far as their level of consciousness, yes.\NIt's like a tack, a tack doesn't calibrate very high, but under the tire of your car,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.16,1:37:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't that it has the power to destroy your life, you understand? It's just the consequence\Nof its linear characteristics. A nail in the road, and your tire hits it, now you can
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.29,1:37:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,turn over. So you're misconceiving it, you're misconceptualizing it by saying, look, the\Nnail has the power to kill five people in the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.44,1:37:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...\NThat's a metal game you're playing with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.92,1:37:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not all viruses are bad, either. Some viruses are...\NYeah, I know, but I get what she's saying. She's misconceiving power.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.42,1:37:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDoesn't have the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.44,1:37:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it just seems we focus a lot of attention on it, you know?\NOh, yes, we do with nails in the tires, too. I sweep them out of my driveway all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.30,1:37:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.\NYeah, I understand her question. It comes up once in a while. Because of the form, say.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.25,1:38:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to thank you for your books and your work, and it's been a great deal to me, and\NI appreciate that. I have a question, and I'm not sure how to ask it, so I'll just talk
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.49,1:38:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,around it, and hopefully it'll come out in some meaningful way. One of your helpers said\NI needed to ask you personally because you don't answer email very much, so I figured
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.98,1:38:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd come up and ask the question. It has to do with the calibration charts and...\NYou're a walking email, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.98,1:38:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NNow they walk around in a human body. They'll do anything to get their... Yeah, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.76,1:38:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't press the delete button. The calibration charts were... On one level, they make a great\Ndeal of sense. In other words, I can tell that certain levels have more energy than
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.67,1:38:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,others, and it just makes a lot of sense.\NYou can intuit it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.49,1:38:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. My question has to do with how accurate is this depending on what one's level is,\Nin other words...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.01,1:39:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The higher your level, the more accurate it is.\NExactly. I'm finding that, for example, within a circle of friends, there'll be just a wild
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.01,1:39:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,range of interpretations about, well, I'm obviously a 600. I'm below 600. I'm below...\NAnybody else had that experience? I don't know, but it just seems to be whoever's doing
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.22,1:39:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the interpreting is going to be higher and higher and higher depending on where they're\Ncoming from.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.74,1:39:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.\NIt just seems to me that there's...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.74,1:39:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, look, it comes with wisdom and experience.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.14,1:39:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell people, don't bother calibrating yourself, because you're not going to get an accurate\Nnumber. Besides, it's irrelevant. When it doesn't mean anything to you anymore, you'll
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.64,1:39:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly know it.\NOne of the questions I have was this misinterpretation of the different calibration levels. Maybe
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.53,1:39:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't do it back then, but something along that line, which led to the caste system\Nin India, for example.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.89,1:39:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Which led to what?\NSomething where...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.89,1:39:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The caste.\NThe caste system.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.89,1:39:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The caste.\NThe caste system.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.04,1:39:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you're labeling people, like, they're untouchables here, or this person's a merchant,\Nthis person's a private level, that type of thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.19,1:40:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. That's...\NYeah. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.19,1:40:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me that the misuse of such a calibration could lead to something like\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.19,1:40:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The misuse of anything, including holy water, can drown you.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.19,1:40:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It can drown in holy water. Babies do it all the time.\NBlessing this baby. I had to run to the bathroom for a second. I come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.19,1:40:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.19,1:40:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.19,1:40:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.19,1:40:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.19,1:40:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.19,1:40:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.38,1:40:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's floating in the christening thing.\NI guess that answers my question.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.84,1:40:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What can be done with truth in what way. You know what I'm saying.\NBack...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.48,1:40:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Affirmative.\NIt's misused or abused you know. But you're mixing classes now. Categories.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.22,1:40:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just thinking in Sedona a million years from now when they unearth\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.28,1:41:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, Hawkinology, you know, and find that this work existed, and trying to make something out of it, I was wondering how they're going.\NWhat kind of ology?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.28,1:41:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hawkinology.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.28,1:41:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hawkinology.\NHawkinology.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.28,1:41:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'll leave some relics.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.28,1:41:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean they'll still be here?\NThey can be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.28,1:41:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of future generations can verify them.\NAnd I've been working on a book, actually, for ten years, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.28,1:41:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been doing kinesiology for a while.\NAnd I wanted to ask your permission to use some of your writing in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.28,1:41:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just send me the quotes you want.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.28,1:41:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll give you formal permission.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.28,1:41:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.28,1:41:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHawkinology.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.69,1:41:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cute.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.69,1:41:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSee, it's the intention with which you use it that determines the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.36,1:41:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.64,1:41:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your work.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.64,1:41:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.64,1:42:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you expand a little bit on the...\NCan you expand a little more on intention?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.64,1:42:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the mechanics of it?\NOn what?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.64,1:42:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention.\NIntention.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.64,1:42:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it matter how long you hold the thought or from what level it comes from?\NWell, intention means what your purpose, your goal is.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.64,1:42:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NFor instance, if your intention or your goal is to disprove kinesiology, you can do it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.84,1:42:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly.\NHow many pennies have I got in my pocket?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.84,1:42:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I don't know.\NHow many times have I heard that?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.84,1:42:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If your intention is to learn, you see, you can tell right away the intention.\NOne is a declaration, one is a denomination, the other one is a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.35,1:42:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell right away before they even open their mouth.\NThis person asks a question, this person makes a negative declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.64,1:42:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NIf you want to understand something, you go to the man, the best person who can understand
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.08,1:43:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it, the best person who knows about it, and you ask them about it.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.36,1:43:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.42,1:43:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I wanted to...\NSome people complicate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.42,1:43:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why they complicate it.\NYes, and I also would like to extend an invitation to you from Mary Olmwake and the Unity Church
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.42,1:43:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of Kahului in Maui to come visit.\NOh, Maui.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.42,1:43:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Maui, well, yeah.\NAre you a good swimmer?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.42,1:43:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I a good swimmer?\NI don't know if I can make it all the way to Hawaii, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.42,1:43:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.42,1:43:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.42,1:43:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.42,1:43:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.96,1:43:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been in Hawaii since World War II.\NI went out through Pearl and I came back through Pearl.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.96,1:43:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan's been to Hawaii.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.96,1:43:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a daughter there.\NMight be doing school there next year.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.25,1:43:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.25,1:43:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDid we do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.25,1:43:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we finish it?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.25,1:43:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we did.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.25,1:43:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a pleasure and such a joy.\NBecause you're God's gift to me, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.50,1:43:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.50,1:43:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.54,1:44:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.78,1:44:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.78,1:44:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.78,1:44:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.81,1:44:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.81,1:44:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.81,1:44:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.84,1:44:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.84,1:44:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord.\NFor the divine presence in the form of these magnificent people.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.84,1:44:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do again, hold in mind, those in need of the love, the feeling of the presence.\NYou see, because you can go through anything, anything when you feel the presence within
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.50,1:44:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you, any kind of agony, any kind of forgiveness, so we pray that the people who need it feel\NFeel the strength of God's love.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.08,1:44:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The strength of God's love.\NEverybody thinks of God's love as a set of flowers and we'll sing pretty songs.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.84,1:44:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NLove is powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.57,1:45:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In a snowbank, everything stopped.\NThe presence of divinity was overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.39,1:45:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Exquisite.\NMelted.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.62,1:45:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It melts with its infinite power.\NIt's exquisitely gentle.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.49,1:45:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Exquisitely soft and gentle.\NSimultaneously, infinitely powerful like ultra steel.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.68,1:45:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to experience it to understand what seems like an ambiguity.\NHow can that be soft, ultra gentle?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.85,1:45:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So exquisite that it melts.\NMelts one.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.56,1:45:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time of infinite power.\NSeems like a strange paradox.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.63,1:45:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have been there will tell you that's what it is.\NExquisitely sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.29,1:45:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentle.\NHealing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.59,1:45:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Warm.\NAnd of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.71,1:46:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what the people need.\NWe pray for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.03,1:46:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord.\NAmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.00,1:46:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.66,1:46:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhere did they find this lovely, uh, did Gabe find this?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.05,1:46:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot who found this pillow.\NGabe, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.21,1:46:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Gabe there?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.59,1:46:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see.\NI can't see where he was.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.31,1:46:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you looking for?\NIs that Gabe there?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.16,1:46:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's Gabe.\NI didn't know where he got this pillow.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.42,1:46:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does this go, Gabe?\NGot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.72,1:46:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThat was great.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.87,1:46:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we had another day, huh?\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.49,1:46:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
